HEADWORD: Mezza majolica
<hw>Mez"za ma*jol"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It. See
<er>Mezzo</er>; <er>Majolica</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Ceramics)</fld>
<def>Italian pottery of the epoch and general character of majolica, but
less brilliantly decorated, esp. such pottery without tin enamel, but
painted and glazed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

